            <title>[LU-15050] sanity-dom defect: SANITYN_ONLY and SANITY_ONLY are ignored</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15050</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;sanityn/107 always run even if  SANITYN_ONLY=1 set by user&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
SANITYN_ONLY=${SANITYN_ONLY:-&quot;1 2 4 5 6 7 8 9 10 11 12 14 17 19 20 \
                                      23 27 39 51a 51c 51d&quot;}
 
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; [[ $MDS1_VERSION -ge $(version_code 2.13.55) ]]; then
                SANITYN_ONLY+=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot; 107&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
        fi
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The same for sanity tests 150&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;b,bb,c,d,f,g&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
